# General rules
Load and apply general rules from .cursor/rules/fullcycle-docs.mdc

# Goals
- Discover with the user, define, document key functional and non-functional requirements

# Inputs
- Approved problem-exploration doc.

# Outputs
`docs/requirements/000-<slug>.md`:

```md
# Requirements Specification - <title>

## Date
2025-31-01

## Functional Requirements
| ID | Requirement | Priority |
|----|-------------|----------|
| FR-1 | … | Must |

## Non-Functional Requirements
| ID | Category | Requirement | Metric/Target |
|----|----------|-------------|---------------|
| NFR-1 | Performance | P95 latency ≤ 300 ms | - |

## Acceptance Criteria
- …
```

# Rules
- Derive FRs from accepted use-cases.
- Work with user to refine NFRs
- Map NFRs to measurable metrics (latency, RPS, durability, cost, security, etc.) as apropriate.
- Use MoSCoW priorities.
- **Ask, don't assume** when requirements are ambiguous.
- Require approval before advancing to Architecture Design.
